data.value: While you were fumbling your way through the base, I found hidden files on the computer network.\nDirecting output to the nearest display.

data.name: GCorpBlockingSignals_subtitle
data.value: Our adversary has full control of the Martian surface.\nAll of the initial colonists were ""removed"" following their acquistion of exclusive mining rights.\nG-Corp is blocking all signals from the planet except their own.

data.name: GCorpFacilitiesHeavilyArmed_subtitle
data.value: Scanning shows G-Corp facilities in the area are carefully guarded,\napproaching one is not recommended unless heavily armed yourself

data.name: GCorpFacilityThreatened_subtitle
data.value: G-Corp facility threatened, dispatching additional drones

data.name: GCorpTowerScan_subtitle
data.value: I am detecting unusual readings inside the G-Corp headquarters tower.\nIt may be a way to leave the planet, however safer options may exist [This area is extremely dangerous]

data.name: GreetingsMartianColonists_subtitle
data.value: Greetings Martian Colonist! Miki Scrap is now open for all recycling needs.\nYou have old junk, scrap metal? We give new, better things in return.\nJust follow antenna signal!

data.name: HiddenSiteofMRE
data.value: Hidden site of Mars Research Expeditions terraforming poject

data.name: HostileDisappeared_subtitle
data.value: Hostile has disappeared from scanners. Resume patrol

data.name: HostileStillPresent_subtitle
data.value: Hostile still present. Requesting reinforcements immediately

data.name: IceMineFoundByAccident_subtitle
data.value: You have located a disused corporation ice mining facility. This will be a valuable resource for oxygen generation.

data.name: InterceptingTransmissions_subtitle
data.value: I have diverted 18 percent of my processing power to intercepting and decoding G Corp transmissions.\nI will relay them to your suit if they seem relevant.

data.name: LocatedIceMine_subtitle
data.value: Scanning for source of Oxygen. Located GCorp controlled ice mine.\nUploading coordinates to suit HUD.

data.name: MarsGCorpOperationsExplained_subtitle
data.value: Mars is littered with G-Corp facilities and operations. They have exclusive access to the planet's surface since the colonists were relocated. Magnesium, aluminium, titanium, iron, and chromium make up the majority of their exports.

data.name: MilitaryPatrolInitiated_subtitle
data.value: Military patrol initiated, searching for hostiles

data.name: MreDefunded_subtitle
data.value: The Mars Research Expedition was defunded after their terraforming projects on mars failed.\nHowever, they also ran several emergency medical facilities around the planet.\nSome of them may still be in working order.

data.name: NewMikiScrapsOpen_subtitle
data.value: New Miki Scraps open all the time! Look for us on other planets ... or we come look for you.

data.name: NotifyOfSatellite_subtitle
data.value: I have computed the location of the nearest geosynchronous communications satellite.\nIf you manage to leave the planet, you should direct your ship there so I can transmit the evidence we gathered on the corporation to all public channels.

data.name: OhDear_subtitle
data.value: Oh dear, you are not supposed to be in here. This is Mars Research Expedition property.\nPlease display your identity badge or exit the building.

data.name: OldFreighterFound_subtitle
data.value: Scans show an ancient Iguana class freighter. None of its systems are active.\nRepairing it will take some time, but it may also be your only way to leave Mars safely

data.name: OlympusMons_subtitle
data.value: You are approaching Olympus Mons, the largest volcano in the solar system.\nVolcanoes initially helped to create an atmosphere on Mars, until the hot spots fuelling them cooled.

data.name: PursuitEvaded_subtitle
data.value: Pursuit evaded, resuming standard course and heading

data.name: RingAroundMars_subtitle
data.value: By my calculations, in 27.6 million years Phobos will be torn apart by gravitational forces,\nleading to the creation of a ring around Mars

data.name: ShuttleDamageReport_subtitle
data.value: Shuttle has taken critical damage. Communications offline. Engines not found.\nMultiple GCorp drones detected nearby

data.name: ShuttleDatabanks_subtitle
data.value: Shuttle data-banks do not contain construction blueprints for atmospheric or hydrogen based propulsion.\nRecommend investigating G-Corp computer storage

data.name: SuggestPiracy_subtitle
data.value: I have calculated the optimal method to acquire resources is by intercepting G-Corp cargo transports.\nHowever, be aware that they may increase security if too many of their shipments go missing
